HEADWORD: Otididae
<hw>Otididae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A family of birds related to
the cranes, most of which are large and ground-running, and comprising
the bustards.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Otididae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
